result.execSummary:
The defendant Zachary M Hurt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Incest with Child, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.06(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: If a Wisconsin State Prison sentence is imposed, outstanding financial obligations shall be paid from all inmate money at a rate of 25% and the balance due as a condition of extended supervision.  If extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with financial obligations owing, a judgment shall be entered.

Defendant shall not be employed in any capacity working with children. 
Defendant shall not enter any establishment where the primary purpose is the sale or service of alcohol.
Defendant shall not have direct or indirect contact with MEHW (dob 10-21-03). 
Defendant shall not possess or use pornography or sexually explicit materials. 
Defendant shall not possess or use a computer or cell phone with internet capability without prior agent approval.
Defendant shall not have contact with any females under age 18 exept incidental contact.

Defendant shall participate in sex offender treatment and all counseling or treatment programs as directed by his supervising agent. 
Defendant shall pay Dept of Corrections supervision fees.
Defendant shall provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Defendant has the right to request expungement of DNA analysis in writing through the Department of Justice.
Defendant shall comply with sex offender registration requirements.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Defendant shall obtain and maintan full time employment or school or a combination thereof.
